In the bottom right corner there is a recommendation. Red means the automated
detector thinks there is an enemy. Please select an option to report.
Green means that the automated detector thinks the images are all clear.

Excellent! So long as the detector is always correct, 
you can focus all your attention on the cursor.
Whoops! Turns out that sometimes there is a false alarm, 
and the automation mistakenly detects an enemy.
Sometimes, the automation is not completely sure about its recommendation.
Here, it is somewhat certain that there is an enemy.
Here, it is somewhat sure the pictures are clear.

These recommendations are more likely to be incorrect than the others.

They can give false alarms and miss the enemy.
 
